62class JSIPCSemaphore : public RefCounted<JSIPCSemaphore> {
63public:
64 static Ref<JSIPCSemaphore> create(IPC::Semaphore&& semaphore = { })
65 {
66 return adoptRef(*new JSIPCSemaphore(WTFMove(semaphore)));
67 }
68
69 JSObjectRef createJSWrapper(JSContextRef);
70 static JSIPCSemaphore* toWrapped(JSContextRef, JSValueRef);
71
72 void encode(IPC::Encoder& encoder) const { m_semaphore.encode(encoder); }
73 IPC::Semaphore exchange(IPC::Semaphore&& semaphore = { })
74 {
75 return std::exchange(m_semaphore, WTFMove(semaphore));
76 }
77
78private:
79 JSIPCSemaphore(IPC::Semaphore&& semaphore)
80 : m_semaphore(WTFMove(semaphore))
81 { }
82
83 static JSClassRef wrapperClass();
84 static JSIPCSemaphore* unwrap(JSObjectRef);
85 static void initialize(JSContextRef, JSObjectRef);
86 static void finalize(JSObjectRef);
87
88 static const JSStaticFunction* staticFunctions();
89
90 static JSValueRef signal(JSContextRef, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception);
91 static JSValueRef waitFor(JSContextRef, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception);
92
93 IPC::Semaphore m_semaphore;
94};

206static JSValueRef createTypeError(JSContextRef context, const String& message)
207{
208 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(toJS(context)->vm());
209 return toRef(JSC::createTypeError(toJS(context), message));
210}
211
212static std::optional<uint64_t> convertToUint64(JSC::JSValue jsValue)
213{
214 if (jsValue.isNumber()) {
215 double value = jsValue.asNumber();
216 if (value < 0 || trunc(value) != value)
217 return std::nullopt;
218 return value;
219 }
220 if (jsValue.isBigInt())
221 return JSC::JSBigInt::toBigUInt64(jsValue);
222 return std::nullopt;
223}

225JSObjectRef JSIPCSemaphore::createJSWrapper(JSContextRef context)
226{
227 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
228 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
229 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
230 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
231 JSObjectRef wrapperObject = JSObjectMake(toGlobalRef(globalObject), wrapperClass(), this);
232 scope.clearException();
233 return wrapperObject;
234}

236JSClassRef JSIPCSemaphore::wrapperClass()
237{
238 static JSClassRef jsClass;
239 if (!jsClass) {
240 JSClassDefinition definition = kJSClassDefinitionEmpty;
241 definition.className = "Semaphore";
242 definition.parentClass = nullptr;
243 definition.staticValues = nullptr;
244 definition.staticFunctions = staticFunctions();
245 definition.initialize = initialize;
246 definition.finalize = finalize;
247 jsClass = JSClassCreate(&definition);
248 }
249 return jsClass;
250}

284JSValueRef JSIPCSemaphore::signal(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
285{
286 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
287 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
288 auto jsIPCSemaphore = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
289 if (!jsIPCSemaphore) {
290 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
291 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
292 }
293
294 jsIPCSemaphore->m_semaphore.signal();
295
296 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
297}
298
299JSValueRef JSIPCSemaphore::waitFor(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
300{
301 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
302 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
303 auto jsIPCSemaphore = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
304 if (!jsIPCSemaphore) {
305 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
306 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
307 }
308
309 if (argumentCount < 1) {
310 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Must specify the timeout in milliseconds as the first argument"_s);
311 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
312 }
313
314 auto jsValue = toJS(globalObject, arguments[0]);
315 Seconds timeout;
316 if (jsValue.isNumber()) {
317 double milliseconds = jsValue.asNumber();
318 if (std::isfinite(milliseconds) && milliseconds > 0)
319 timeout = Seconds::fromMilliseconds(milliseconds);
320 }
321 if (!timeout) {
322 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Timeout must be a positive number"_s);
323 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
324 }
325
326 auto result = jsIPCSemaphore->m_semaphore.waitFor(timeout);
327
328 return JSValueMakeBoolean(context, result);
329}

397JSValueRef JSSharedMemory::readBytes(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
398{
399 auto jsSharedMemory = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
400 if (!jsSharedMemory) {
401 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
402 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
403 }
404
405 size_t offset = 0;
406 size_t length = jsSharedMemory->m_sharedMemory->size();
407
408 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
409 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
410 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
411 if (argumentCount) {
412 auto offsetValue = convertToUint64(toJS(globalObject, arguments[0]));
413 if (!offsetValue) {
414 *exception = createTypeError(context, "The first argument must be a byte offset to read"_s);
415 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
416 }
417 if (*offsetValue > length)
418 offset = length;
419 else
420 offset = *offsetValue;
421 length -= offset;
422 }
423
424 if (argumentCount > 1) {
425 auto lengthValue = convertToUint64(toJS(globalObject, arguments[1]));
426 if (!lengthValue) {
427 *exception = createTypeError(context, "The second argument must be the number of bytes to read"_s);
428 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
429 }
430 if (*lengthValue < length)
431 length = *lengthValue;
432 }
433
434 auto arrayBuffer = JSC::ArrayBuffer::create(static_cast<uint8_t*>(jsSharedMemory->m_sharedMemory->data()) + offset, length);
435 JSC::JSArrayBuffer* jsArrayBuffer = nullptr;
436 if (auto* structure = globalObject->arrayBufferStructure(arrayBuffer->sharingMode()))
437 jsArrayBuffer = JSC::JSArrayBuffer::create(vm, structure, WTFMove(arrayBuffer));
438 if (!jsArrayBuffer) {
439 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to create the array buffer for the read bytes"_s);
440 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
441 }
442
443 return toRef(jsArrayBuffer);
444}
445
446struct ArrayBufferData {
447 void* buffer { nullptr };
448 size_t length { 0 };
449};
450
451static ArrayBufferData arrayBufferDataFromValueRef(JSContextRef context, JSTypedArrayType type, JSValueRef valueRef, JSValueRef* exception)
452{
453 auto objectRef = JSValueToObject(context, valueRef, exception);
454 if (!objectRef)
455 return { };
456
457 void* buffer = nullptr;
458 if (type == kJSTypedArrayTypeArrayBuffer)
459 buffer = JSObjectGetArrayBufferBytesPtr(context, objectRef, exception);
460 else
461 buffer = JSObjectGetTypedArrayBytesPtr(context, objectRef, exception);
462
463 if (!buffer)
464 return { };
465
466 size_t length;
467 if (type == kJSTypedArrayTypeArrayBuffer)
468 length = JSObjectGetArrayBufferByteLength(context, objectRef, exception);
469 else
470 length = JSObjectGetTypedArrayByteLength(context, objectRef, exception);
471
472 return { buffer, length };
473}
474
475JSValueRef JSSharedMemory::writeBytes(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
476{
477 auto jsSharedMemory = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
478 if (!jsSharedMemory) {
479 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
480 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
481 }
482
483 auto type = argumentCount ? JSValueGetTypedArrayType(context, arguments[0], exception) : kJSTypedArrayTypeNone;
484 if (type == kJSTypedArrayTypeNone) {
485 *exception = createTypeError(context, "The first argument must be an array buffer or a typed array"_s);
486 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
487 }
488
489 auto data = arrayBufferDataFromValueRef(context, type, arguments[0], exception);
490 if (!data.buffer) {
491 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Could not read the buffer"_s);
492 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
493 }
494
495 size_t offset = 0;
496 size_t length = data.length;
497 size_t sharedMemorySize = jsSharedMemory->m_sharedMemory->size();
498
499 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
500 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
501 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
502
503 if (argumentCount > 1) {
504 auto offsetValue = convertToUint64(toJS(globalObject, arguments[1]));
505 if (!offsetValue) {
506 *exception = createTypeError(context, "The second argument must be a byte offset to write"_s);
507 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
508 }
509 if (*offsetValue >= sharedMemorySize) {
510 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Offset is too big"_s);
511 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
512 }
513 offset = *offsetValue;
514 }
515
516 if (argumentCount > 2) {
517 auto lengthValue = convertToUint64(toJS(globalObject, arguments[2]));
518 if (!lengthValue) {
519 *exception = createTypeError(context, "The third argument must be the number of bytes to write"_s);
520 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
521 }
522 if (*lengthValue >= sharedMemorySize - offset || *lengthValue > length) {
523 *exception = createTypeError(context, "The number of bytes to write is too big"_s);
524 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
525 }
526 length = *lengthValue;
527 }
528
529 memcpy(static_cast<uint8_t*>(jsSharedMemory->m_sharedMemory->data()) + offset, data.buffer, length);
530
531 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
532}

601static RefPtr<IPC::Connection> processTargetFromArgument(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSValueRef valueRef, JSValueRef* exception)
602{
603 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(globalObject->vm());
604 auto name = toJS(globalObject, valueRef).toWTFString(globalObject);
605 if (scope.exception())
606 return nullptr;
607
608 if (name == "UI")
609 return WebProcess::singleton().parentProcessConnection();
610#if ENABLE(GPU_PROCESS)
611 if (name == "GPU")
612 return &WebProcess::singleton().ensureGPUProcessConnection().connection();
613#endif
614 if (name == "Networking")
615 return &WebProcess::singleton().ensureNetworkProcessConnection().connection();
616
617 *exception = toRef(JSC::createTypeError(globalObject, "Target process must be UI, GPU, or Networking"_s));
618 return nullptr;
619}
620
621void JSIPC::addMessageListener(JSMessageListener::Type type, JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
622{
623 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
624 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
625 auto jsIPC = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
626 if (!jsIPC) {
627 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
628 return;
629 }
630
631 if (argumentCount < 1) {
632 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Must specify the target process as the first argument"_s);
633 return;
634 }
635
636 auto connection = processTargetFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[0], exception);
637 if (!connection)
638 return;
639
640 std::unique_ptr<JSMessageListener> listener;
641 if (argumentCount >= 2 && JSValueIsObject(context, arguments[1])) {
642 auto listenerObjectRef = JSValueToObject(context, arguments[1], exception);
643 if (JSObjectIsFunction(context, listenerObjectRef))
644 listener = makeUnique<JSMessageListener>(*jsIPC, type, context, listenerObjectRef);
645 }
646
647 if (!listener) {
648 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Must specify a callback function as the second argument"_s);
649 return;
650 }
651
652 connection->addMessageObserver(*listener);
653 jsIPC->m_messageListeners.append(makeUniqueRefFromNonNullUniquePtr(WTFMove(listener)));
654}
655
656JSValueRef JSIPC::addIncomingMessageListener(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
657{
658 addMessageListener(JSMessageListener::Type::Incoming, context, thisObject, argumentCount, arguments, exception);
659 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
660}
661
662JSValueRef JSIPC::addOutgoingMessageListener(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
663{
664 addMessageListener(JSMessageListener::Type::Outgoing, context, thisObject, argumentCount, arguments, exception);
665 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
666}

668static std::optional<uint64_t> destinationIDFromArgument(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSValueRef valueRef, JSValueRef* exception)
669{
670 auto jsValue = toJS(globalObject, valueRef);
671 auto result = convertToUint64(jsValue);
672 if (!result)
673 *exception = toRef(JSC::createTypeError(globalObject, "destinationID must be an integer"_s));
674 return result;
675}

677static std::optional<uint64_t> messageIDFromArgument(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSValueRef valueRef, JSValueRef* exception)
678{
679 auto jsValue = toJS(globalObject, valueRef);
680 auto result = convertToUint64(jsValue);
681 if (!result)
682 *exception = toRef(JSC::createTypeError(globalObject, "messageID must be an integer"_s));
683 return result;
684}
685
686static bool encodeTypedArray(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSContextRef context, JSValueRef valueRef, JSTypedArrayType type, JSValueRef* exception)
687{
688 ASSERT(type != kJSTypedArrayTypeNone);
689
690 auto data = arrayBufferDataFromValueRef(context, type, valueRef, exception);
691 if (!data.buffer)
692 return false;
693
694 encoder.encodeFixedLengthData(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(data.buffer), data.length, 1);
695 return true;
696}
697
698template<typename PointType> bool encodePointType(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSC::JSObject* jsObject, JSC::CatchScope& scope)
699{
700 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
701 auto jsX = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "x"_s));
702 if (scope.exception() || !jsX.isNumber())
703 return false;
704 auto jsY = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "y"_s));
705 if (scope.exception() || !jsY.isNumber())
706 return false;
707 encoder << PointType(jsX.asNumber(), jsY.asNumber());
708 return true;
709}
710
711template<typename RectType> bool encodeRectType(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSC::JSObject* jsObject, JSC::CatchScope& scope)
712{
713 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
714 auto jsX = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "x"_s));
715 if (scope.exception() || !jsX.isNumber())
716 return false;
717 auto jsY = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "y"_s));
718 if (scope.exception() || !jsY.isNumber())
719 return false;
720 auto jsWidth = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "width"_s));
721 if (scope.exception() || !jsWidth.isNumber())
722 return false;
723 auto jsHeight = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "height"_s));
724 if (scope.exception() || !jsHeight.isNumber())
725 return false;
726 encoder << RectType(jsX.asNumber(), jsY.asNumber(), jsWidth.asNumber(), jsHeight.asNumber());
727 return true;
728}
729
730template<typename IntegralType> bool encodeNumericType(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSC::JSValue jsValue)
731{
732 if (jsValue.isBigInt()) {
733 // FIXME: Support negative BigInt.
734 uint64_t result = JSC::JSBigInt::toBigUInt64(jsValue);
735 encoder << static_cast<IntegralType>(result);
736 return true;
737 }
738 if (!jsValue.isNumber())
739 return false;
740 double value = jsValue.asNumber();
741 encoder << static_cast<IntegralType>(value);
742 return true;
743}

745#if ENABLE(GPU_PROCESS)
746template <typename ObjectIdentifierType>
747std::optional<ObjectIdentifier<ObjectIdentifierType>> getObjectIdentifierFromProperty(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSC::JSObject* jsObject, ASCIILiteral propertyName, JSC::CatchScope& scope)
748{
749 auto jsPropertyValue = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(globalObject->vm(), propertyName));
750 if (scope.exception())
751 return std::nullopt;
752 auto number = convertToUint64(jsPropertyValue);
753 if (!number)
754 return std::nullopt;
755 return makeObjectIdentifier<ObjectIdentifierType>(*number);
756}

758static bool encodeRemoteRenderingBackendCreationParameters(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSC::JSObject* jsObject, JSC::CatchScope& scope)
759{
760 auto identifier = getObjectIdentifierFromProperty<RenderingBackendIdentifierType>(globalObject, jsObject, "identifier"_s, scope);
761 if (!identifier)
762 return false;
763
764 auto jsSemaphore = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(globalObject->vm(), "semaphore"_s));
765 if (scope.exception())
766 return false;
767 auto semaphoreObject = makeRefPtr(JSIPCSemaphore::toWrapped(toRef(globalObject), toRef(jsSemaphore)));
768 if (!semaphoreObject)
769 return false;
770
771 auto pageProxyID = getObjectIdentifierFromProperty<WebPageProxyIdentifierType>(globalObject, jsObject, "pageProxyID"_s, scope);
772 if (!pageProxyID)
773 return false;
774
775 auto pageID = getObjectIdentifierFromProperty<WebCore::PageIdentifierType>(globalObject, jsObject, "pageID"_s, scope);
776 if (!pageID)
777 return false;
778
779 auto semaphore = semaphoreObject->exchange();
780 RemoteRenderingBackendCreationParameters parameters { *identifier, WTFMove(semaphore), *pageProxyID, *pageID };
781 encoder << parameters;
782 semaphoreObject->exchange(WTFMove(parameters.resumeDisplayListSemaphore));
783 return true;
784}
785#endif
786
787static bool encodeSharedMemory(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSC::JSObject* jsObject, JSC::CatchScope& scope)
788{
789 auto jsSharedMemoryValue = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(globalObject->vm(), "value"_s));
790 if (scope.exception())
791 return false;
792 auto jsSharedMemory = makeRefPtr(JSSharedMemory::toWrapped(toRef(globalObject), toRef(jsSharedMemoryValue)));
793 if (!jsSharedMemory)
794 return false;
795
796 uint32_t dataSize = jsSharedMemory->size();
797
798 auto jsDataSizeValue = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(globalObject->vm(), "dataSize"_s));
799 if (scope.exception())
800 return false;
801 if (!jsDataSizeValue.isUndefined()) {
802 if (auto dataSizeValue = convertToUint64(jsDataSizeValue))
803 dataSize = *dataSizeValue;
804 }
805
806 auto jsProtectionValue = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(globalObject->vm(), "protection"_s));
807 if (scope.exception())
808 return false;
809 if (jsProtectionValue.isUndefined())
810 return false;
811 auto protectionValue = jsProtectionValue.toWTFString(globalObject);
812 if (scope.exception())
813 return false;
814 auto protection = SharedMemory::Protection::ReadWrite;
815 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(protectionValue, "readonly"))
816 protection = SharedMemory::Protection::ReadOnly;
817 else if (!equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(protectionValue, "readwrite"))
818 return false;
819
820 encoder << SharedMemory::IPCHandle { jsSharedMemory->createHandle(protection), dataSize };
821 return true;
822}
823
824static bool encodeSemaphore(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, JSC::JSValue jsValue, JSC::CatchScope& scope)
825{
826 auto jsIPCSemaphore = makeRefPtr(JSIPCSemaphore::toWrapped(toRef(globalObject), toRef(jsValue)));
827 if (!jsIPCSemaphore)
828 return false;
829
830 jsIPCSemaphore->encode(encoder);
831 return true;
832}
833
834static bool encodeArgument(IPC::Encoder&, JSIPC&, JSContextRef, JSValueRef, JSValueRef* exception);
835
836struct VectorEncodeHelper {
837 Ref<JSIPC> jsIPC;
838 JSContextRef context;
839 JSValueRef valueRef;
840 JSValueRef* exception;
841 bool& success;
842
843 void encode(IPC::Encoder& encoder) const
844 {
845 if (!success)
846 return;
847 success = encodeArgument(encoder, jsIPC.get(), context, valueRef, exception);
848 }
849};
850
851enum class ArrayMode { Tuple, Vector };
852static bool encodeArrayArgument(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSIPC& jsIPC, ArrayMode arrayMode, JSContextRef context, JSValueRef valueRef, JSValueRef* exception)
853{
854 auto objectRef = JSValueToObject(context, valueRef, exception);
855 ASSERT(objectRef);
856
857 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
858 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
859 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
860 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(globalObject->vm());
861 auto* jsObject = toJS(objectRef);
862
863 auto jsLength = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "length"_s));
864 if (scope.exception())
865 return false;
866 if (!jsLength.isNumber()) {
867 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Array length is not a number"_s);
868 return false;
869 }
870 auto length = jsLength.asNumber();
871
872 Vector<VectorEncodeHelper> vector;
873 bool success = true;
874 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
875 auto itemRef = JSObjectGetPropertyAtIndex(context, objectRef, i, exception);
876 if (!itemRef)
877 return false;
878 vector.append(VectorEncodeHelper { jsIPC, context, itemRef, exception, success });
879 }
880 if (arrayMode == ArrayMode::Tuple) {
881 for (auto& item : vector)
882 item.encode(encoder);
883 } else
884 encoder << vector;
885 return success;
886}
887
888static bool encodeArgument(IPC::Encoder& encoder, JSIPC& jsIPC, JSContextRef context, JSValueRef valueRef, JSValueRef* exception)
889{
890 auto objectRef = JSValueToObject(context, valueRef, exception);
891 if (!objectRef)
892 return false;
893
894 if (auto type = JSValueGetTypedArrayType(context, objectRef, exception); type != kJSTypedArrayTypeNone)
895 return encodeTypedArray(encoder, context, objectRef, type, exception);
896
897 if (JSValueIsArray(context, objectRef))
898 return encodeArrayArgument(encoder, jsIPC, ArrayMode::Tuple, context, objectRef, exception);
899
900 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
901 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
902 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
903 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(globalObject->vm());
904 auto* jsObject = toJS(globalObject, objectRef).getObject();
905 ASSERT(jsObject);
906 auto jsType = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "type"_s));
907 if (scope.exception())
908 return false;
909
910 auto type = jsType.toWTFString(globalObject);
911 if (scope.exception())
912 return false;
913
914 if (type == "IntPoint") {
915 if (!encodePointType<WebCore::IntPoint>(encoder, globalObject, jsObject, scope)) {
916 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert IntPoint"_s);
917 return false;
918 }
919 return true;
920 }
921
922 if (type == "FloatPoint") {
923 if (!encodePointType<WebCore::IntPoint>(encoder, globalObject, jsObject, scope)) {
924 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert FloatPoint"_s);
925 return false;
926 }
927 return true;
928 }
929
930 if (type == "IntRect") {
931 if (!encodeRectType<WebCore::IntRect>(encoder, globalObject, jsObject, scope)) {
932 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert IntRect"_s);
933 return false;
934 }
935 return true;
936 }
937
938 if (type == "FloatRect") {
939 if (!encodeRectType<WebCore::FloatRect>(encoder, globalObject, jsObject, scope)) {
940 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert FloatRect"_s);
941 return false;
942 }
943 return true;
944 }
945
946#if ENABLE(GPU_PROCESS)
947 if (type == "RemoteRenderingBackendCreationParameters") {
948 if (!encodeRemoteRenderingBackendCreationParameters(encoder, globalObject, jsObject, scope)) {
949 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert RemoteRenderingBackendCreationParameters"_s);
950 return false;
951 }
952 return true;
953 }
954#endif
955
956 if (type == "SharedMemory") {
957 if (!encodeSharedMemory(encoder, globalObject, jsObject, scope)) {
958 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert SharedMemory"_s);
959 return false;
960 }
961 return true;
962 }
963
964 if (type == "FrameInfoData") {
965 auto webFrame = makeRefPtr(jsIPC.webFrame());
966 if (!webFrame) {
967 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to get the frame"_s);
968 return false;
969 }
970 encoder << webFrame->info();
971 return true;
972 }
973
974 auto jsValue = jsObject->get(globalObject, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "value"_s));
975 if (scope.exception())
976 return false;
977
978 if (type == "Semaphore") {
979 if (!encodeSemaphore(encoder, globalObject, jsValue, scope)) {
980 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to convert Semaphore"_s);
981 return false;
982 }
983 return true;
984 }
985
986 if (type == "Vector") {
987 if (!jsValue.isObject() || !jsValue.inherits<JSC::JSArray>(vm)) {
988 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Vector value must be an array"_s);
989 return false;
990 }
991 return encodeArrayArgument(encoder, jsIPC, ArrayMode::Vector, context, toRef(globalObject, jsValue), exception);
992 }
993
994 if (type == "String") {
995 if (jsValue.isUndefinedOrNull()) {
996 encoder << String { };
997 return true;
998 }
999 auto string = jsValue.toWTFString(globalObject);
1000 if (scope.exception())
1001 return false;
1002 encoder << string;
1003 return true;
1004 }
1005
1006 if (type == "URL") {
1007 if (jsValue.isUndefinedOrNull()) {
1008 encoder << URL { };
1009 return true;
1010 }
1011 auto string = jsValue.toWTFString(globalObject);
1012 if (scope.exception())
1013 return false;
1014 encoder << URL { URL { }, string };
1015 return true;
1016 }
1017
1018 if (type == "RegistrableDomain") {
1019 if (jsValue.isUndefinedOrNull()) {
1020 encoder << WebCore::RegistrableDomain { };
1021 return true;
1022 }
1023 auto string = jsValue.toWTFString(globalObject);
1024 if (scope.exception())
1025 return false;
1026 encoder << WebCore::RegistrableDomain { URL { URL { }, string } };
1027 return true;
1028 }
1029
1030 if (type == "RGBA") {
1031 if (!jsValue.isNumber()) {
1032 *exception = createTypeError(context, "RGBA value should be a number"_s);
1033 return false;
1034 }
1035 uint32_t rgba = jsValue.asNumber();
1036 encoder << WebCore::Color { WebCore::asSRGBA(WebCore::PackedColor::RGBA(rgba)) };
1037 return true;
1038 }
1039
1040 bool numericResult;
1041 if (type == "bool")
1042 numericResult = encodeNumericType<bool>(encoder, jsValue);
1043 else if (type == "double")
1044 numericResult = encodeNumericType<double>(encoder, jsValue);
1045 else if (type == "float")
1046 numericResult = encodeNumericType<float>(encoder, jsValue);
1047 else if (type == "int8_t")
1048 numericResult = encodeNumericType<int8_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1049 else if (type == "int16_t")
1050 numericResult = encodeNumericType<int16_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1051 else if (type == "int32_t")
1052 numericResult = encodeNumericType<int32_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1053 else if (type == "int64_t")
1054 numericResult = encodeNumericType<int64_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1055 else if (type == "uint8_t")
1056 numericResult = encodeNumericType<uint8_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1057 else if (type == "uint16_t")
1058 numericResult = encodeNumericType<uint16_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1059 else if (type == "uint32_t")
1060 numericResult = encodeNumericType<uint32_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1061 else if (type == "uint64_t")
1062 numericResult = encodeNumericType<uint64_t>(encoder, jsValue);
1063 else {
1064 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Bad type name"_s);
1065 return false;
1066 }
1067 if (!numericResult) {
1068 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Failed to encode a number"_s);
1069 return false;
1070 }
1071 return true;
1072}
1073
1074
1075static JSC::JSObject* jsResultFromReplyDecoder(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, IPC::MessageName messageName, IPC::Decoder& decoder)
1076{
1077 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1078 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
1079
1080 auto arrayBuffer = JSC::ArrayBuffer::create(decoder.buffer(), decoder.length());
1081 JSC::JSArrayBuffer* jsArrayBuffer = nullptr;
1082 if (auto* structure = globalObject->arrayBufferStructure(arrayBuffer->sharingMode()))
1083 jsArrayBuffer = JSC::JSArrayBuffer::create(vm, structure, WTFMove(arrayBuffer));
1084 if (!jsArrayBuffer) {
1085 throwException(globalObject, scope, JSC::createTypeError(globalObject, "Failed to create the array buffer for the reply"_s));
1086 return nullptr;
1087 }
1088
1089 auto jsReplyArguments = jsValueForReplyArguments(globalObject, messageName, decoder);
1090 if (!jsReplyArguments) {
1091 throwException(globalObject, scope, JSC::createTypeError(globalObject, "Failed to decode the reply"_s));
1092 return nullptr;
1093 }
1094
1095 if (jsReplyArguments->isEmpty()) {
1096 throwException(globalObject, scope, JSC::createTypeError(globalObject, "Failed to convert the reply to an JS array"_s));
1097 return nullptr;
1098 }
1099
1100 auto catchScope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1101 JSC::JSObject* jsResult = constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1102 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(catchScope, nullptr);
1103
1104 jsResult->putDirect(vm, vm.propertyNames->arguments, *jsReplyArguments);
1105 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(catchScope, nullptr);
1106
1107 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "buffer"), jsArrayBuffer);
1108 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(catchScope, nullptr);
1109
1110 return jsResult;
1111}
1112
1113JSValueRef JSIPC::sendMessage(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
1114{
1115 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1116 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
1117 auto jsIPC = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
1118 if (!jsIPC) {
1119 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
1120 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1121 }
1122
1123 if (argumentCount < 3) {
1124 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Must specify the target process, desination ID, and message ID as the first three arguments"_s);
1125 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1126 }
1127
1128 auto connection = processTargetFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[0], exception);
1129 if (!connection)
1130 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1131
1132 auto destinationID = destinationIDFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[1], exception);
1133 if (!destinationID)
1134 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1135
1136 auto messageID = messageIDFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[2], exception);
1137 if (!messageID)
1138 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1139
1140 auto messageName = static_cast<IPC::MessageName>(*messageID);
1141 auto encoder = makeUniqueRef<IPC::Encoder>(messageName, *destinationID);
1142
1143 JSValueRef returnValue = JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1144
1145 bool hasReply = !!messageReplyArgumentDescriptions(messageName);
1146 if (hasReply) {
1147 uint64_t listenerID = IPC::nextAsyncReplyHandlerID();
1148 encoder.get() << listenerID;
1149
1150 JSObjectRef resolve;
1151 JSObjectRef reject;
1152ALLOW_NEW_API_WITHOUT_GUARDS_BEGIN
1153 returnValue = JSObjectMakeDeferredPromise(context, &resolve, &reject, exception);
1154ALLOW_NEW_API_WITHOUT_GUARDS_END
1155 if (!returnValue)
1156 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1157
1158 JSGlobalContextRetain(JSContextGetGlobalContext(context));
1159 JSValueProtect(context, resolve);
1160 JSValueProtect(context, reject);
1161 IPC::addAsyncReplyHandler(*connection, listenerID, [messageName, context, resolve, reject](IPC::Decoder* replyDecoder) {
1162 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1163 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1164 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
1165
1166 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1167 auto* jsResult = jsResultFromReplyDecoder(globalObject, messageName, *replyDecoder);
1168 if (auto* exception = scope.exception()) {
1169 scope.clearException();
1170 JSValueRef arguments[] = { toRef(globalObject, exception) };
1171 JSObjectCallAsFunction(context, reject, reject, 1, arguments, nullptr);
1172 } else {
1173 JSValueRef arguments[] = { toRef(globalObject, jsResult) };
1174 JSObjectCallAsFunction(context, resolve, resolve, 1, arguments, nullptr);
1175 }
1176
1177 JSValueUnprotect(context, reject);
1178 JSValueUnprotect(context, resolve);
1179 JSGlobalContextRelease(JSContextGetGlobalContext(context));
1180 });
1181 }
1182
1183 if (argumentCount > 3) {
1184 if (!encodeArgument(encoder.get(), *jsIPC, context, arguments[3], exception))
1185 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1186 }
1187
1188 // FIXME: Add the support for specifying IPC options.
1189
1190 connection->sendMessage(WTFMove(encoder), { });
1191
1192 return returnValue;
1193}
1194
1195JSValueRef JSIPC::sendSyncMessage(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
1196{
1197 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1198 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
1199 auto jsIPC = makeRefPtr(toWrapped(context, thisObject));
1200 if (!jsIPC) {
1201 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
1202 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1203 }
1204
1205 if (argumentCount < 4) {
1206 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Must specify the target process, desination ID, and message ID as the first three arguments"_s);
1207 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1208 }
1209
1210 auto connection = processTargetFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[0], exception);
1211 if (!connection)
1212 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1213
1214 auto destinationID = destinationIDFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[1], exception);
1215 if (!destinationID)
1216 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1217
1218 auto messageID = messageIDFromArgument(globalObject, arguments[2], exception);
1219 if (!messageID)
1220 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1221
1222 Seconds timeout;
1223 {
1224 auto jsValue = toJS(globalObject, arguments[3]);
1225 if (!jsValue.isNumber()) {
1226 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Timeout must be a number"_s);
1227 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1228 }
1229 timeout = Seconds { jsValue.asNumber() };
1230 }
1231
1232 // FIXME: Support the options.
1233
1234 IPC::Connection::SyncRequestID syncRequestID;
1235 auto messageName = static_cast<IPC::MessageName>(*messageID);
1236 auto encoder = connection->createSyncMessageEncoder(messageName, *destinationID, syncRequestID);
1237
1238 if (argumentCount > 4) {
1239 if (!encodeArgument(encoder.get(), *jsIPC, context, arguments[4], exception))
1240 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1241 }
1242
1243 if (auto replyDecoder = connection->sendSyncMessage(syncRequestID, WTFMove(encoder), timeout, { })) {
1244 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(globalObject->vm());
1245 auto* jsResult = jsResultFromReplyDecoder(globalObject, messageName, *replyDecoder);
1246 if (scope.exception()) {
1247 *exception = toRef(globalObject, scope.exception());
1248 scope.clearException();
1249 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1250 }
1251 return toRef(globalObject, jsResult);
1252 }
1253
1254 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1255}
1256
1257JSValueRef JSIPC::createSemaphore(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
1258{
1259 return JSIPCSemaphore::create()->createJSWrapper(context);
1260}
1261
1262JSValueRef JSIPC::createSharedMemory(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef, JSObjectRef thisObject, size_t argumentCount, const JSValueRef arguments[], JSValueRef* exception)
1263{
1264 if (!toWrapped(context, thisObject)) {
1265 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Wrong type"_s);
1266 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1267 }
1268
1269 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1270 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1271 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
1272
1273 auto size = argumentCount ? convertToUint64(toJS(globalObject, arguments[0])) : std::optional<uint64_t> { };
1274 if (!size) {
1275 *exception = createTypeError(context, "Must specify the size"_s);
1276 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1277 }
1278
1279 return JSSharedMemory::create(*size)->createJSWrapper(context);
1280}

1287 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);

1289 return JSValueMakeNumber(context, pageSize());

1328JSValueRef JSIPC::retrieveID(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef thisObject, JSValueRef* exception, const WTF::Function<uint64_t(JSIPC&)>& callback)
1329{
1330 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1331 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1332 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
1333
1334 RefPtr<JSIPC> wrapped = toWrapped(context, thisObject);
1335 if (!wrapped) {
1336 *exception = toRef(JSC::createTypeError(toJS(context), "Wrong type"_s));
1337 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1338 }
1339
1340 auto id = callback(*wrapped);
1341 JSC::JSCell* jsValue = JSC::JSBigInt::createFrom(globalObject, id);
1342 return toRef(vm, jsValue);
1343}
1344
1345static JSC::JSValue createJSArrayForArgumentDescriptions(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, std::optional<Vector<IPC::ArgumentDescription>>&& argumentDescriptions)
1346{
1347 if (!argumentDescriptions)
1348 return JSC::jsNull();
1349
1350 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1351 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1352 JSC::JSObject* argumentsArray = JSC::constructEmptyArray(globalObject, nullptr);
1353 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1354
1355 for (unsigned argumentIndex = 0; argumentIndex < argumentDescriptions->size(); ++argumentIndex) {
1356 auto& description = argumentDescriptions->at(argumentIndex);
1357 JSC::JSObject* jsDescriptions = constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1358 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1359
1360 argumentsArray->putDirectIndex(globalObject, argumentIndex, jsDescriptions);
1361 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1362
1363 jsDescriptions->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "name"), JSC::jsString(vm, String(description.name)));
1364 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1365
1366 jsDescriptions->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "type"), JSC::jsString(vm, String(description.type)));
1367 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1368
1369 jsDescriptions->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "optional"), JSC::jsBoolean(description.isOptional));
1370 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1371
1372 if (description.enumName) {
1373 jsDescriptions->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "enum"), JSC::jsString(vm, String(description.enumName)));
1374 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::jsTDZValue());
1375 }
1376 }
1377 return argumentsArray;
1378}
1379
1380JSValueRef JSIPC::messages(JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef thisObject, JSStringRef, JSValueRef* exception)
1381{
1382 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1383 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1384 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
1385
1386 auto* impl = toWrapped(context, thisObject);
1387 if (!impl) {
1388 *exception = toRef(JSC::createTypeError(toJS(context), "Wrong type"_s));
1389 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1390 }
1391
1392 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1393 JSC::JSObject* messagesObject = constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1394 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1395
1396 auto nameIdent = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "name");
1397 auto replyArgumentsIdent = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "replyArguments");
1398 auto isSyncIdent = JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "isSync");
1399 for (unsigned i = 0; i < static_cast<unsigned>(IPC::MessageName::Last); ++i) {
1400 auto name = static_cast<IPC::MessageName>(i);
1401
1402 JSC::JSObject* dictionary = constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1403 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1404
1405 dictionary->putDirect(vm, nameIdent, JSC::JSValue(i));
1406 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1407
1408 auto argumentDescriptions = createJSArrayForArgumentDescriptions(globalObject, IPC::messageArgumentDescriptions(name));
1409 if (argumentDescriptions.isEmpty())
1410 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1411 dictionary->putDirect(vm, vm.propertyNames->arguments, argumentDescriptions);
1412 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1413
1414 auto replyArgumentDescriptions = createJSArrayForArgumentDescriptions(globalObject, IPC::messageReplyArgumentDescriptions(name));
1415 if (replyArgumentDescriptions.isEmpty())
1416 return JSValueMakeUndefined(context);
1417 dictionary->putDirect(vm, replyArgumentsIdent, replyArgumentDescriptions);
1418 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1419
1420 dictionary->putDirect(vm, isSyncIdent, JSC::jsBoolean(messageIsSync(name)));
1421 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1422
1423 messagesObject->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, description(name)), dictionary);
1424 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSValueMakeUndefined(context));
1425 }
1426
1427 return toRef(vm, messagesObject);
1428}
1429
1430JSMessageListener::JSMessageListener(JSIPC& jsIPC, Type type, JSContextRef context, JSObjectRef callback)
1431 : m_jsIPC(makeWeakPtr(jsIPC))
1432 , m_type(type)
1433 , m_context(context)
1434 , m_callback(callback)
1435{
1436 auto* globalObject = toJS(context);
1437 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1438 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
1439
1440 auto catchScope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1441
1442 // We can't retain the global context here as that would cause a leak
1443 // since this object is supposed to live as long as the global object is alive.
1444 JSC::PrivateName uniquePrivateName;
1445 globalObject->putDirect(vm, uniquePrivateName, toJS(globalObject, callback));
1446
1447 UNUSED_PARAM(catchScope);
1448}
1449
1450void JSMessageListener::didReceiveMessage(const IPC::Decoder& decoder)
1451{
1452 if (m_type != Type::Incoming)
1453 return;
1454
1455 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_jsIPC);
1456 auto protectOwnerOfThis = makeRef(*m_jsIPC);
1457 auto* globalObject = toJS(m_context);
1458 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
1459
1460 auto mutableDecoder = IPC::Decoder::create(decoder.buffer(), decoder.length(), nullptr, { });
1461 auto* description = jsDescriptionFromDecoder(globalObject, *mutableDecoder);
1462
1463 JSValueRef arguments[] = { description ? toRef(globalObject, description) : JSValueMakeUndefined(m_context) };
1464 JSObjectCallAsFunction(m_context, m_callback, m_callback, std::size(arguments), arguments, nullptr);
1465}
1466
1467void JSMessageListener::willSendMessage(const IPC::Encoder& encoder, OptionSet<IPC::SendOption>)
1468{
1469 if (m_type != Type::Outgoing)
1470 return;
1471
1472 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_jsIPC);
1473 auto protectOwnerOfThis = makeRef(*m_jsIPC);
1474 auto* globalObject = toJS(m_context);
1475 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(globalObject->vm());
1476
1477 auto decoder = IPC::Decoder::create(encoder.buffer(), encoder.bufferSize(), nullptr, { });
1478 auto* description = jsDescriptionFromDecoder(globalObject, *decoder);
1479
1480 JSValueRef arguments[] = { description ? toRef(globalObject, description) : JSValueMakeUndefined(m_context) };
1481 JSObjectCallAsFunction(m_context, m_callback, m_callback, WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(arguments), arguments, nullptr);
1482}
1483
1484JSC::JSObject* JSMessageListener::jsDescriptionFromDecoder(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, IPC::Decoder& decoder)
1485{
1486 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1487 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1488
1489 auto* jsResult = constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1490 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1491
1492 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "name"), JSC::JSValue(static_cast<unsigned>(decoder.messageName())));
1493 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1494
1495 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "description"), JSC::jsString(vm, IPC::description(decoder.messageName())));
1496 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1497
1498 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "destinationID"), JSC::JSValue(decoder.destinationID()));
1499 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1500
1501 if (decoder.isSyncMessage()) {
1502 IPC::Connection::SyncRequestID syncRequestID;
1503 if (decoder.decode(syncRequestID)) {
1504 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "syncRequestID"), JSC::JSValue(syncRequestID.toUInt64()));
1505 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1506 }
1507 } else if (messageReplyArgumentDescriptions(decoder.messageName())) {
1508 if (uint64_t listenerID = 0; decoder.decode(listenerID)) {
1509 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "listenerID"), JSC::JSValue(listenerID));
1510 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1511 }
1512 }
1513
1514 auto arrayBuffer = JSC::ArrayBuffer::create(decoder.buffer(), decoder.length());
1515 if (auto* structure = globalObject->arrayBufferStructure(arrayBuffer->sharingMode())) {
1516 if (auto* jsArrayBuffer = JSC::JSArrayBuffer::create(vm, structure, WTFMove(arrayBuffer))) {
1517 jsResult->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "buffer"), jsArrayBuffer);
1518 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1519 }
1520 }
1521
1522 auto jsReplyArguments = jsValueForArguments(globalObject, decoder.messageName(), decoder);
1523 if (jsReplyArguments) {
1524 jsResult->putDirect(vm, vm.propertyNames->arguments, jsReplyArguments->isEmpty() ? JSC::jsNull() : *jsReplyArguments);
1525 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, nullptr);
1526 }
1527
1528 return jsResult;
1529}
1530
1531void inject(WebPage& webPage, WebFrame& webFrame, WebCore::DOMWrapperWorld& world)
1532{
1533 auto* globalObject = webFrame.coreFrame()->script().globalObject(world);
1534
1535 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1536 JSC::JSLockHolder lock(vm);
1537 auto scope = DECLARE_CATCH_SCOPE(vm);
1538 auto wrapped = JSIPC::create(webPage, webFrame);
1539 JSObjectRef wrapperObject = JSObjectMake(toGlobalRef(globalObject), JSIPC::wrapperClass(), wrapped.ptr());
1540 globalObject->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "IPC"), toJS(globalObject, wrapperObject));
1541
1542 scope.clearException();
1543}

1551template<>
1552JSC::JSValue jsValueForDecodedArgumentValue(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, IPC::Semaphore&& value)
1553{
1554 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1555 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
1556 auto* object = JSC::constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1557 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1558 object->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "type"_s), JSC::jsNontrivialString(vm, "Semaphore"));
1559 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1560 auto jsValue = toJS(globalObject, WebKit::IPCTestingAPI::JSIPCSemaphore::create(WTFMove(value))->createJSWrapper(toRef(globalObject)));
1561 object->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "value"_s), jsValue);
1562 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1563 return object;
1564}
1565
1566template<> JSC::JSValue jsValueForDecodedArgumentValue(JSC::JSGlobalObject* globalObject, WebKit::SharedMemory::IPCHandle&& value)
1567{
1568 using SharedMemory = WebKit::SharedMemory;
1569 using Protection = WebKit::SharedMemory::Protection;
1570
1571 auto& vm = globalObject->vm();
1572 auto scope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
1573 auto* object = JSC::constructEmptyObject(globalObject, globalObject->objectPrototype());
1574 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1575 object->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "type"_s), JSC::jsNontrivialString(vm, "SharedMemory"));
1576 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1577
1578 auto protection = Protection::ReadWrite;
1579 auto sharedMemory = SharedMemory::map(value.handle, protection);
1580 if (!sharedMemory) {
1581 protection = Protection::ReadOnly;
1582 sharedMemory = SharedMemory::map(value.handle, protection);
1583 if (!sharedMemory)
1584 return JSC::JSValue();
1585 }
1586
1587 auto jsValue = toJS(globalObject, WebKit::IPCTestingAPI::JSSharedMemory::create(sharedMemory.releaseNonNull())->createJSWrapper(toRef(globalObject)));
1588 object->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "value"_s), jsValue);
1589 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1590
1591 object->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "dataSize"_s), JSC::JSValue(value.dataSize));
1592 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1593
1594 object->putDirect(vm, JSC::Identifier::fromString(vm, "protection"_s), JSC::jsNontrivialString(vm, protection == Protection::ReadWrite ? "ReadWrite" : "ReadOnly"));
1595 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(scope, JSC::JSValue());
1596
1597 return object;
1598}
